parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal noises
loss of power
stalling
smoke or fire from the engine compartment
oil leaks
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission failures can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
delayed or sudden loss of pressure
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify owners of engine recalls can lead to engine failure, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: No warning lights or messages prior to engine failure
and owners not receiving recall notifications.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine failure, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Oil leaks
smoke or fire from the engine compartment
and low oil pressure warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Warning Lights or Messages
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to provide warning lights or messages can lead to engine failure, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: No warning lights or messages prior to engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes make an abnormal noise
the vehicle shakes violently when braking
the brake pads
rotors
and calipers fail and need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the vehicle fails to start
an abnormal ticking sound is heard when starting the vehicle
the check engine warning light is illuminated
an electrical short circuit to the battery and starter is diagnosed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas cap can cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, leading to unnecessary repairs and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The check engine warning light is illuminated
the gas cap needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine performance can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power when climbing hills
the vehicle slows down when accelerating
the gas pedal needs to be mashed to the floor to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Bearing Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to bearing wear can cause the vehicle to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud knocking or rattling noise from the engine
loss of power
engine stalling
oil leaks
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Soft or spongy clutch pedal
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
delayed or sudden loss of pressure
and inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
loud noises or vibrations when shifting
and warning lights on the dashboard.
